@node Porting
@chapter Porting
@cindex porting

@menu
* Porting Organization::
@end menu

This guide is largely focused on porting @dfn{STREAMS} drivers, modules and
applications programs that act in the capacity of an X.25 User.  Whereas other
documents tend to focus on simply porting drivers for specific interface cards,
that topic is adequately addressed elsewhere for the @cite{Linux} kernel.
Whenever a network device driver has been written for a device under
@cite{Linux}, using @cite{Linux} paradigms and procedures, it can automatically
work with @dfn{X.25}.  Therefore, this guide focusses on the differences between
the @dfn{X.25} interfaces that would be experienced by the X.25 User:
@dfn{STREAMS} modules that push over X.25 Streams; @dfn{STREAMS} drivers under
which X.25 Streams are linked; and applications programs that access the X.25
interface directly as a user-space program.

@cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} and each of its add-on packages, including
@cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}}, ship with a wide assortment of manual pages.  Most
manual pages contain a section entitled ``@cite{COMPATIBILITY}'' that provides
compatibility and porting information for various mainstream @cite{UNIX}
implementations.  For information on the minor differences in the @dfn{STREAMS}
environment, see the @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} package,
@command{streams-@value{VERSION_STREAMS}}.

There are hundreds of manual pages in the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package
for @dfn{X.25}.  These manual pages can be explored best by starting with the
@manref{x25(7)} manual page.  The manual pages document both X.25 Revision
2.0.0 standard behaviour, as well as the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}}
implementations of extension primitives, input-output controls, and features
documented for other operating systems including @cite{AIX}, @cite{HP-UX},
@cite{IRIX}, @cite{OSF}, @cite{PowerMAX}, @cite{Solaris}, @cite{SVR 4},
@cite{SVR 4.2MP}, @cite{UnixWare 7}.  Although each of the @dfn{X.25} related
manual pages of supported functions, primitives and structures provide
compatibilty and porting information, this document attempts to gather together
pertinent information concerning porting @dfn{X.25} modules, drivers and
applications programs from various @dfn{UNIX} operating systems supporting
@dfn{STREAMS} and @dfn{X.25} to @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}}.

Where there is discrepencies between this documentation and the manual pages
that ship with the package, the manual pages are controlling.  This is because
this guide is updated less frequently that the documented functionality in the
manual pages.

