@node AIX NPI Addressing
@subsection AIX NPI Addressing

@subsubsection AIX NPI Driver Naming

For an application to use NPI, it would typically follow these steps:

@enumerate
@item Open a Stream to the packet driver.
@item Pushe the NPI module.
@item Bind the application to the NPI module.
@item Submit a connection request to establish a connection between the local
and remote X.25 systems.
@item Once the connection becomes established, transfer the required data.
@item Disconnect the two systems.
@end enumerate

The example @cite{AIXlink/X.25} gives is:

@smallexample
dev = open("/dev/x25pkt", O_RDWR);
/* assumes good return value */
ioctl(dev, I_PUSH, "npi"); /* uses the streams library push ioctl */
@end smallexample

